KitInfo.Description: ATSAMD21BLDC24V-STK is a low voltage BLDC, PMSM motor control starter kit. Supported by the Atmel Studio integrated development platform, the kit provides easy access to the features of the ATSAMD21J18A MCU and explains how to integrate the device in a custom motor control application.

KitInfo.Title: ATREB215-XPRO
KitInfo.Description: The Microchip ATREB215-XPRO is an Xplained Pro Extension board targeted for evaluating the features and performance of the Microchip multi-band radio transceiver AT86RF215. This Kit can be used for conducted and radiated lab measurements in 2.4GHz; can also be used only for conducted lab measurements in various sub-1 GHz bands (389.5 - 510MHz and 779 - 1020MHz). It provides wireless functionality to Xplained Pro evaluation platform; also a hardware platform for software development and customer product prototyping.

KitInfo.Title: ATREB215-XPRO-A

KitInfo.Title: Microchip High Voltage Motor Control Driver Board
KitInfo.Description: ATSAMBLDCHV is a high voltage motor control driver board for ATSAMBLDCHV-STK starter kit. Driver board supports voltage upto 400V and 750W. The hardware contains IPM based motor control driver, current and voltage sensing circuit, Hall and Encoder interface, fault protection circuits and a pluggable MCU card interface. In addition, the kit supports two stage interleaved PFC based on boost converter and it's voltage and current sensing circuitry.

KitInfo.Title: Motor Control SAMC21 MCU card
KitInfo.Description: ATSAMC21J18AMOTOR is a pluggable MCU card for Microchip BLDC, PMSM Motor Control Starter Kits. MCU card supports ATSAMD21BLDC24V-STK, the low voltage motor control starter kit and ATSAMBLDCHV-STK, the high voltage motor control starter kit. The kits contains a driver board hardware with half bridge power MOSFET/IPM drivers, current and voltage sensing circuit, Hall and Encoder interface, fault protection circuits and a pluggable MCU card. ATSAMC21MOTOR MCU card has ATSAMC21J18A controller and on board debugger. Supported by the Atmel Studio integrated development platform, the kit provides easy access to the features of the ATSAMC21J18A MCU and explains how to integrate the device in a custom motor control application.

KitInfo.Title: Afero-Mod2-XPRO
KitInfo.Description: The Afero-Mod2-XPRO is an IoT development kit that connects any Microchip microcontroller with an XPRO interface to the Afero Modulo-2 IoT reference design board. The kit provides easy and rapid firmware development, connecting IoT applications to the Afero Cloud over Wi-Fi or Bluetooth® Smart technology. The Modulo-2 can operate either within the socketed environment of the adapter board or, with minimal programming, autonomously. The Afero Modulo-2 board gives you a simple and easy-to-use IoT reference design.

KitInfo.Title: SAM G55 Xplained Pro AWS
KitInfo.Description: The Zero Touch for AWS IoT Secure Provisioning Platform for AWS IoT offers the industry’s first end-to-end security solution for Internet of Things (IoT) devices that connect to the Amazon Web Services’ (AWS) cloud. The product was developed jointly with AWS and will help IoT devices complying quickly and easily with AWS’s mutual authentication IoT security model. The new security model states that a device must use mutual authentication with a remote server to be authorized on the AWS cloud. Adding Microchip’s pre-configured ECC508 device and software kit to a system is now the simplest and most secure solution available to connect to the AWS IoT service.

KitInfo.Title: IA611 Xplained Pro
KitInfo.Description: The IA61x is a family of "always-on" Smart Microphones featuring Voice Wake and Voice ID keyword detectors, an audio buffer, and Knowles’ proven high performance acoustic SiSonicTM MEMS technology in a single, miniature, MEMS microphone package. The IA61x offers flexibility by supporting the most relevant audio and data interfaces, including is a special version with a SoundWire® interface making it the World’s first SoundWire® Microphone. Its integrated programmable DSP is made available to 3rd party algorithms, enabling unlimited creativity. The solution pushes the system performance to ultra low power with its custom core design, and accelerates time to market with its unique combined hardware, software and firmware package.

KitInfo.Title: 565 LCD Adapter
KitInfo.Description: This is a 565 LCD adapter for the new generation of Xplained Ultra & Curiosity Ultra Development kits. The 565 LCD adapter allows for the mapping of 16-bit color to 24-bit color that is needed by most LCD displays. These adapters come standard with some kits but can also be purchased separately. This can be used with the 4.3" WQVGA display (AC320005-4) or the QVGA (AC320005-5).

KitInfo.Title: SSD1963 LCD Controller
KitInfo.Description: The SSD1963 LCD controller is an external LCD controller for parallel LCD interfaces for the new generation of Xplained Ultra & Curiosity Ultra Development kits. The controller can take in either a 8-bit or 16-bit parallel interface (8080 mode or 6800 mode) and generate an LCD output for a panel. The part has 1,215KB of SDRAM internal to the chip capable of supporting 864 x 480 x 24bit graphics content. Its display interface supports common RAM-less LCD driver of color depth up to 24 bit-per-pixel. This can be used with the 4.3" WQVGA display (AC320005-4) or the QVGA (AC320005-5).

KitInfo.Title: 24-Bit LCD Adapter
KitInfo.Description: This is a 24-Bit LCD adapter for the new generation of Xplained Ultra & Curiosity Ultra Development kits. This is meant for MCUs that can drive a 24-bit LCD directly from the MCU or trying to pass data through to an external controller in a 1:1 configuration. These adapters come standard with some kits but can also be purchased separately. This can be used with the 4.3" WQVGA display (AC320005-4) or the QVGA (AC320005-5).
